author: National Geographic
description:
Presented by National Geographic Society in partnership with Rolex.

On Christmas Eve, a National Geographic Society expedition spotted an Antarctic gonate squid at the outer edge of the Powell Basin in the Southern Ocean.

This rare species had previously only been seen in fishing nets or as remnants in the stomachs of fished marine animals. The exciting find helps researchers form theories around its habitats and daily life: https://on.natgeo.com/BRYT202506101

Rolex and the National Geographic Society are partnering on science-based expeditions to explore, study, and document change in the planet’s unique regions. #PerpetualPlanet
title: The first sighting of an Antarctic gonate squid #PerpetualPlanet
